UML:TaggedValue.value: Application schema to allow delivery of Utility data (water, gas, electricity) in GML
Values for resultMethod are: Manual Reading Customer Value Calculated
Device that records water consumption at a location
Meter ID - should be a persistent ID in form of http URI
Date that the recorded value was made or inferred
Method used to calculate reading ("Manual Reading", "Customer Value", "Calculated")

Specifies the result units of measure. Note that the same units of measure must be used for all results for any reading (eg peak, off-peak, feed-in, self-generated results must all have the same units).
Features to deliver utility supply data
Finishing date and time of the supply period
Starting date and time of the supply period
The name of the region being supplied by energy or water
Units used to record the supply data
The identifier of the Utility supplying the energy or water
The name of the Utility supplying the energy or water
The geographical area for the data from the Utility supplying the energy or water
The amount of water supplied to customers
The amount of water supplied to the environment
The ID of the water outflow
The amount of electricity supplied for the period defined by the startDeliveryTime to endDeliveryTime.
